                         <content-note style="NORMAL">a subsidiary body of the UN General Assembly</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">mandated to promote universal respect for the protection of all human rights and fundamental freedoms for all</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">addresses and makes recommendations on situations of violations of human rights</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">supports human rights education and learning and provides advisory services, technical assistance and capacity-building support</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">serves as a platform for dialogue on thematic issues connected with human rights</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">in 2024 the HRC was maintaining the following subsidiary bodies: a Social Forum; an Expert Mechanism on the Rights of Indigenous People; an Expert Mechanism on the Right to Development; a Forum on Minority Issues; a Forum on Business and Human Rights; and a Forum on Human Rights, Democracy and the Rule of Law</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">the HRC Advisory Committee functions as a think tank under the direction of the Council</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">issues mandates, under an OHCHR-supported system of Special Procedures (comprising individual special rapporteurs, independent experts, or working groups) to report and advise on civil, cultural, economic, political and social human rights from a thematic or country-focused perspective</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">may establish independent investigations as formal Commissions of Inquiry (CoIs), Commissions on Human Rights (CoHRs), Fact-Finding Missions (FFMs), International Teams of Experts (ITEs), Groups of Eminent International and Regional Experts (GEEs), Groups of Human Rights Experts (GHREs), and other UN Independent Investigations (UN IIs)</content-note>
