                         <content-note style="NORMAL">special sessions of the Council can be called at the request of at least one-third of mem. states</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">the 36th special session, held in May 2023, addressed the human rights impacts of the conflict in Sudan</content-note>
                         <content-note style="NORMAL">the third consecutive 5-year cycle of the Universal Periodic Review (UPR) was being undertaken, under HRC auspices, during 2022-27, providing for a full assessment of the human rights situation in UN member states as well as consideration of violations or other relevant issues and the sharing of best practices</content-note>
                         <stats>47 mems, elected by the UN General Assembly, serve 3-year terms (13 mems from African states, Asia-Pacific: 13, Latin America and the Caribbean: 8; Western Europe and other: 7; Eastern Europe: 6)</stats>
